cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on improving the performance of deep learning models through data parallelism. It may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it deals with multi-GPU computations and inter-GPU communication. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as deep learning is commonly used in this field. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also possible categories as they are related to the use of deep learning and parallel computing in data analysis and processing.
